# Design Token Best Practices

When working with design tokens and design systems, follow these conventions:

## Naming Conventions

1. **Use semantic names** - Name tokens by purpose, not appearance
   - ✅ `--color-text-primary` 
   - ❌ `--color-dark-gray`

2. **Use consistent prefixes** - Group related tokens
   - `--color-*` for colors
   - `--space-*` for spacing
   - `--font-*` for typography
   - `--radius-*` for border radius
   - `--shadow-*` for shadows

3. **Use scales for variants** - Number or size-based scales
   - `--space-1`, `--space-2`, `--space-4`
   - `--font-size-sm`, `--font-size-base`, `--font-size-lg`

## Token Organization

```css
:root {
  /* Colors - organized by category */
  --color-primary: #...;
  --color-primary-hover: #...;
  
  --color-bg-primary: #...;
  --color-bg-secondary: #...;
  
  --color-text-primary: #...;
  --color-text-secondary: #...;
  
  /* Typography */
  --font-family-sans: ...;
  --font-size-base: ...;
  
  /* Spacing */
  --space-1: ...;
  --space-2: ...;
  
  /* Effects */
  --shadow-sm: ...;
  --radius-md: ...;
}
```

## Dark Mode Support

Always provide dark mode variants:

```css
/* Method 1: Media query */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  :root {
    --color-bg-primary: #111827;
    --color-text-primary: #F9FAFB;
  }
}

/* Method 2: Class-based */
.dark {
  --color-bg-primary: #111827;
  --color-text-primary: #F9FAFB;
}
```

## Usage Guidelines

1. **Always use tokens** - Never hardcode colors, sizes, or other design values
2. **Fallback values** - Provide fallbacks for critical tokens
3. **Document tokens** - Add comments explaining token purposes
4. **Single source of truth** - Define tokens in one place only

## Example Usage

```css
/* ✅ Good - Using tokens */
.button {
  background-color: var(--color-primary);
  padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-size: var(--font-size-base);
}

/* ❌ Bad - Hardcoded values */
.button {
  background-color: #5E6AD2;
  padding: 8px 16px;
  border-radius: 6px;
  font-size: 14px;
}
```

## Accessibility

1. Ensure color contrast meets WCAG 2.1 AA standards (4.5:1 for text)
2. Test tokens with color blindness simulators
3. Provide sufficient focus indicators
4. Don't rely on color alone for meaning
